  "text": "One of the biggest methodological dangers of big data analyses is insufficient understanding of the underlying sample and denominators. It's often not enough to understand how many people have \"liked\" a Facebook status update, clicked on a link, or \"retweeted\" a message without having a sense of how many people saw and chose to -or not to-take that option. That kind of normalization is rarely done, or may even be actively decided against because the results start appearing more complex or more trivial [CITATION_1] .",
